    {
      "key": "abdfff4e-50aa-4eb9-8aa7-09e1b538d1ac",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "abdfff4e-50aa-4eb9-8aa7-09e1b538d1ac",
        "lesson_activity.key": "54811cc2-5273-4374-972e-182fd49db3e8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4ea2ace9-1e76-419f-be5b-574730181363",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\">Slide</td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">Lesson Guide</td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/ac3d5d744975ee355a92b77b55ed37c0-Slide29.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Reveal one vocabulary term & definition at a time. Briefly introduce each term as a preview of what students will learn in this lesson.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/e2ce27c30228425469740920f31f0aca-Slide30.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Discuss:</strong> What are the benefits of efficient code? \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Discussion Goal:</strong> Using the definition of efficient as a guide, students might start to guess that efficient code is shorter code. \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br />Teaching Tip\n\t\t<br />It is okay if there are not many ideas or connections at this point in the lesson. They will be learning all about functions and efficient code throughout the lesson.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/1046c1c0833e38737642cd0bd899c9e1-Slide31.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Introduce the objectives of this lesson. \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> Today, we will get to experiment with a very powerful code in our programs! We will learn how to save a list of actions and reuse them without reprogramming them using something called a function. The shorter our programs are, the easier it is for the computer to read them, plus they’re easier for us to change if we need to.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/a5c05178c30cc678b76923bb38e8f352-Slide32.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> Dance routines are very similar to functions in computer science! \n\t\t<br />\u000b<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Click the slide to trigger the animation and show the dance function being named and defined. \u000b<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> First, the routine is named and the dance steps are defined. Once they learn the routine, the dancer remembers the steps and the order to do them whenever they hear the​​ name of the dance. \n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Click the slide to trigger the animation to show the Macarena function being used (called). \n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> It is much easier to tell the dancer to do the dance using just one word: Macarena!\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/34a8c48edea6391f96c071e238a0bbfc-Slide33.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <strong>Do This:</strong> Explain the warm up activity and allow students to work independently or in pairs. They will make a new dance using the dance moves in the chart. \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br />Teacher Tip \n\t\t<br />In this activity the 3 part dance in equivalent to a computer program. The dance moves are like functions and the steps are like individual coding blocks.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/a38e29e439c10bcac61758f3bb470153-Slide34.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Finish the warm up activity with an explanation of how functions can be used to make code more efficient and easier to use. They will be practicing customizing and creating functions in code in the next activity in Music Lab.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n</table>    \n    "
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4ea2ace9-1e76-419f-be5b-574730181363",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ae7f1c03-e67f-4bf6-a09f-4e213e5f1fd1"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f531f38e-7142-431c-8b59-96e04a453dd0",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Video Intro"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f531f38e-7142-431c-8b59-96e04a453dd0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "eb3dbace-f6fe-46cd-8e5a-0901a1957364"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1e2f3b12-e527-4850-917e-e9b72e7ba66e",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Skill Building"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1e2f3b12-e527-4850-917e-e9b72e7ba66e",
