      }
    },
    {
      "key": "09bfb736-752a-40e7-abaf-2ea4278c2379",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Remix & Freeplay"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "09bfb736-752a-40e7-abaf-2ea4278c2379",
        "lesson_activity.key": "eb3dbace-f6fe-46cd-8e5a-0901a1957364"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fc9b743e-20a1-4932-81b3-004a10011ede",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\">Slide</td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">Lesson Guide</td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/316cd8cb919274618ef529ae01b6230a-Slide36.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Watch the video on level 1 together as a class. \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Discuss:</strong> (Optional) What does a music producer do?\n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Discussion Goal:</strong> Students will understand that a producer is someone who puts all of the pieces of the music together. They will  move and work on functions with chunks of music to make it sound great.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/9a6cbeb483fb1aac2bbff69d8dcd6a9a-Slide37.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Run level 2 together as a class. Guide students to notice the repetition of the play together block. Make a connection to the activity in the warm up and encourage students to consider the use of a function in place of the repeated code.\n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Transition:</strong> Have students transition to continuing the lesson on their own devices. They will work on levels 3-10 independently.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/0eab112102f8425ecf5e88ec6f02b52f-Slide38.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> Read the instructions for each level and try to complete the code. Press the Run button to try it out. If something is not quite right you will get a hint under the instructions. When you’ve successfully completed the challenge, a new message and a Continue button will appear. Click Continue to move to the next level and move at your speed. \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Circulate:</strong> Encourage students to read the instructions and hints on each level as you circulate. Ask guiding questions to support students if they get stuck.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n</table>    \n    "
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fc9b743e-20a1-4932-81b3-004a10011ede",
        "lesson_activity.key": "eb3dbace-f6fe-46cd-8e5a-0901a1957364"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2cd93f46-82cb-4a99-a539-55eb1dfd69f9",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\">Slide</td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">Lesson Guide</td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/203e17237687c91827071a89369f675d-Slide40.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Review the objectives of the lesson. Have students show a thumbs up/down/sideways to reflect on whether they reached each objective.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"width: 25%\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/2f412e651130ff9d47bf98949cc032d8-Slide41.PNG\"></td>\n    <td style=\"width: 75%\">\n      <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Do This:</strong> Have students set up for a quick Turn & Talk to reexamine the Question of the Day. Some supportive leading questions might be: Why do we use functions instead of rewwriting out every single line of code? If you were a computer could you read a short paragraph or a long story quicker? What if we want to make a change to the code? \n\t\t<br />\n\t\t<br /><i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> Take turns listening and answering the Question of the Day. Give me a thumbs up after you both have shared your answers.\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n\n</table>    \n    "
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2cd93f46-82cb-4a99-a539-55eb1dfd69f9",
